.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS2poU0TSowa3IoGp-0xyFLLlEAw3ESxgFwbw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:548;s:6:"height";i:735;s:6:"source";s:47:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/8796161761008987/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:38:{i:0;s:269:"The chair of the Federal Reserve known formally as the Chair of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System is the head of the central banking system of the United States and the active executive officer of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System.";i:1;s:201:"Directors Promote Effective Functioning of the Federal Reserve System Reserve Bank boards of directors help maintain effective oversight of Reserve Banks and ensure that Reserve Banks operate smoothly.";i:2;s:79:"Directors also assist the Federal Reserves monetary policy responsibilities by.";i:3;s:169:"The Board of Governors is led by a chairman who directs the Feds staff runs Fed board meetings and testifies before Congress when called to do so and as required by law.";i:4;s:127:"The Federal Reserve System often referred to as the Federal Reserve or simply the Fed is the central bank of the United States.";i:5;s:126:"It was created by the Congress to provide the nation with a safer more flexible and more stable monetary and financial system.";i:6;s:122:"The Federal Reserve was created on December 23 1913 when President Woodrow Wilson signed the Federal Reserve Act into law.";i:7;s:179:"The DfE states that it is the Chairs role to make sure that everyone on the board understands what is expected of them and receives appropriate induction training and development.";i:8;s:132:"The Chair should encourage governors to work together as an effective team helping them build their skills knowledge and experience.";i:9;s:35:"Chair of the Federal Reserve Board.";i:10;s:57:"Powell became the Chair of the Board of Governors on Feb.";i:11;s:168:"Governors actively lead committees that study prevailing economic issuesfrom affordable housing and consumer banking laws to interstate banking and electronic commerce.";i:12;s:64:"The Board of Governors also exercises broad supervisory control.";i:13;s:32:"Whats the Role of the Fed Chair.";i:14;s:101:"The Federal Reserve chair sets the direction and tone of both the Federal Reserve Board and the FOMC.";i:15;s:57:"The current chairman is Jerome Powell a Fed board member.";i:16;s:32:"His term as chair runs from Feb.";i:17;s:14:"5 2018 to Feb.";i:18;s:105:"The chairman also guides the Feds powerful Open Market Committee which sets Fed policy on interest rates.";i:19;s:32:"While the chairman only has one.";i:20;s:184:"The Board of Governors led by the Fed chair is responsible for running the institution that is the Federal Reserve and all that is under its purview monetary policy regulatory matters.";i:21;s:54:"Over time the role of the executive branch and the US.";i:22;s:77:"Beginning in 1936 the Secretary of the Treasury no longer served on the FOMC.";i:23;s:187:"The Federal Reserve Board moved to its own building in 1937 and the Federal Reserve gained independence in the setting of monetary policy with the Treasury-Federal Reserve Accord in 1951.";i:24;s:125:"12 Federal Reserve Banks each of which is responsible for overseeing a specific geographical region within the United States.";i:25;s:164:"The Federal Open Market Committee FOMC which oversees the nations open market operations and makes important decisions about interest rates and the supply of money.";i:26;s:68:"Members of the Federal Reserve Board are appointed by the president.";i:27;s:111:"As required by the Federal Reserve Act of 1913 each Federal Reserve bank is supervised by a board of directors.";i:28;s:235:"These boards are composed of three classes of directors A B and C with three members in each class who are from outside the Reserve bank and are familiar with economic and credit conditions in their respective Federal Reserve district.";i:29;s:149:"The Senate Committee responsible for vetting a Federal Reserve vice chair and vice chair for supervision nominees is the Senate Committee on Banking.";i:30;s:31:"Duties of the Fed vice —Åhairs.";i:31;s:161:"The vice chair of the Board shall serve in the absence of the chair as leader of the Federal Reserve system until chairs replacement was installed by the Senate.";i:32;s:26:"The Federal Reserve Board.";i:33;s:139:"Also known as the Board of Governors the Reserve Board is composed of seven members nominated by the president and confirmed by the Senate.";i:34;s:141:"The job of the board which convenes in Washington DC is to guide the Fed and strive to fulfill the five key functions of the Federal Reserve.";i:35;s:29:"O To hold reserve monies for.";i:36;s:93:"Few officials in Washington enjoy the power and autonomy of the chair of the Federal Reserve.";i:37;s:63:"They act as a spokesperson for the central bank negotiate with.";}}